Which version of numpy and matplotlib do you have installed?
You can use the following to obtain them:

python -c "import matplotlib; import numpy as np; print matplotlib.__version__; print np.__version__"

I suspect you're using an old version of matplotlib (before 1.5.0) are are being affected by matplotlib/matplotlib#5209

body:
Which version of numpy and matplotlib do you have installed?
You can use the following to obtain them:

```
python -c "import matplotlib; import numpy as np; print matplotlib.__version__; print np.__version__"
```

I suspect you're using an old version of matplotlib (before 1.5.0) are are being affected by https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/issues/5209
